## Testing

### Unit Tests

```typescript
describe("cleanupPreview", () => {
  it("calls all cleanup steps in order", async () => {
    const mockDockerStop = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);
    const mockDockerRemove = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);
    const mockPortRelease = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);
    const mockCaddyRemoveRoute = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);
    const mockDockerRmi = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);
    const mockDbUpdate = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);

    // ... inject mocks ...

    await cleanupPreview({
      db: mockDb,
      projectSlug: "myapp",
      prNumber: 42,
      deployment: {
        id: "deploy-id",
        containerId: "container-abc123",
        port: 4001,
        dockerImageTag: "myapp:pr-42-a1b2c3d",
      },
    });

    expect(mockDockerStop).toHaveBeenCalledWith("container-abc123", { timeout: 30 });
    expect(mockDockerRemove).toHaveBeenCalledWith("container-abc123");
    expect(mockPortRelease).toHaveBeenCalledWith(4001);
    expect(mockCaddyRemoveRoute).toHaveBeenCalledWith("pr-42--myapp.localhost");
    expect(mockDbUpdate).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it("continues cleanup if container stop fails", async () => {
    const mockDockerStop = vi.fn().mockRejectedValue(new Error("Container not found"));
    const mockPortRelease = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);
    const mockCaddyRemoveRoute = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);

    await cleanupPreview({ /* ... options with mocks ... */ });

    // Port release and Caddy route removal should still be called
    expect(mockPortRelease).toHaveBeenCalled();
    expect(mockCaddyRemoveRoute).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it("continues cleanup if port release fails", async () => {
    const mockDockerStop = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);
    const mockPortRelease = vi.fn().mockRejectedValue(new Error("DB error"));
    const mockCaddyRemoveRoute = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined);

    await cleanupPreview({ /* ... options with mocks ... */ });

    // Caddy route removal should still be called
    expect(mockCaddyRemoveRoute).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it("handles null containerId gracefully", async () => {
    const mockDockerStop = vi.fn();

    await cleanupPreview({
      db: mockDb,
      projectSlug: "myapp",
      prNumber: 42,
      deployment: {
        id: "deploy-id",
        containerId: null,   // No container to stop
        port: 4001,
        dockerImageTag: null,
      },
    });

    expect(mockDockerStop).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it("handles null port gracefully", async () => {
    const mockPortRelease = vi.fn();

    await cleanupPreview({
      db: mockDb,
      projectSlug: "myapp",
      prNumber: 42,
      deployment: {
        id: "deploy-id",
        containerId: "container-id",
        port: null,   // No port to release
        dockerImageTag: null,
      },
    });

    expect(mockPortRelease).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });
});
```

### Integration Tests

- Trigger cleanup for a running preview: verify container stops, port is freed, route is removed
- Trigger cleanup twice for the same preview: verify second call completes without errors
- Trigger cleanup for a preview that was already partially cleaned up (container stopped, port still allocated)

### Manual Verification

1. Open a PR, wait for preview deployment
2. Verify preview is accessible at `pr-{N}--{slug}.yourdomain.dev`
3. Close the PR
4. Verify:
   - `docker ps` no longer shows the preview container
   - `curl https://pr-{N}--{slug}.yourdomain.dev` returns 502 or no route
   - Database shows deployment status as `archived`
   - `docker images | grep pr-{N}` returns no results
5. Reopen the PR (optional): verify a new preview can be created

---

## Output

After this step:
- Preview deployments are fully cleaned up when PRs are closed or merged
- No orphaned containers, ports, or Caddy routes after cleanup
- Preview Docker images are deleted and do not count toward retention limits
- Cleanup is resilient -- individual step failures do not prevent remaining cleanup
- The full Phase 7 preview deployment lifecycle is complete: create -> update -> cleanup
